## Overview
<!-- The Clarification Log is a transversal artefact that tracks questions, ambiguities, and information gaps throughout the project. This document covers Phase 2 additions and status updates for items carried over from Phase 1. -->
This log records all questions and clarifications raised during Phase 2 — Requirements and Baseline. Unresolved clarifications introduce ambiguity into requirements and must be resolved before Gate B.

**Individual Clarification Entries:** See [clarification-entry.md.template](../clarification-entry.md.template) for the standard entry format used when logging new clarifications mid-phase.

**Escalation Path for CRITICAL Items:** Any clarification marked as CRITICAL severity must be escalated to the Requirements Lead within 24 hours. If not resolved within {{critical_resolution_sla}} working days, escalate to the Project Manager and formally notify the Project Sponsor.

